		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />As I understand it, "pinout" pages are supposed to describe what each pin does, and how they're wired into a particular board goes in the board family's page.
<br />
<br />As for /CS vs. /OE: is there really a difference between the two for mask ROM chips? I was always taught that the difference between /CS and /OE is that /CS must be asserted for a write to complete, and /OE need not.

		

